Getting started with the LLVM C API
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

See accompanying blog post by Paul Smith at:
https://pauladamsmith.com/blog/2015/01/how-to-get-started-with-llvm-c-api.html

Tested with LLVM 3.8.0.

To use on Ubuntu, install LLVM and CLANG:

    sudo apt-get install clang-3.8 llvm-3.8

Once LLVM is installed, clone this repo, cd to it, and run:

    $ make
    $ ./sum 42 99
    141
